-- Mexico Stocks: Grupo Mexico, Asur, Ica, Homex Are Active
-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 2012-04-10T21:19:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-10/mexico-stocks-aeroportuario-pacifico-asur-homex-are-active.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Mexico  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the close of trading.  The IPC  index  fell 1 percent to 39,035.17.  Grupo Aeroportuario del Sureste SAB  (ASURB MM), the
operator of airports in southern Mexico, rose 0.4 percent to
93.38 pesos, extending its rally to five days. Traffic climbed
9.1 percent in March from a year earlier, according to a
statement to the Mexican stock exchange on April 4.  Building-related companies led Mexican stocks lower as
Spanish and Italian bond yields rose, spurring concern about
 Europe ’s debt crisis.  Desarrolladora Homex SAB (HOMEX*)  , Mexico’s largest
homebuilder, fell 4.5 percent to 35.41 pesos.  Empresas Ica SAB (ICA*) 
, the country’s biggest construction company, dropped
4.5 percent to 21.86 pesos.  Grupo Mexico SAB (GMEXICOB)  , the country’s largest
mining company, fell 1.7 percent to 38.62 pesos. Copper futures
declined as import demand declined in  China , the world’s largest
user of industrial metals.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan J. Levin in Mexico City at 
